      "message": "the correct namespace for yang models should be used.\nyou can build the api example file using a new yang that imports all the other yangs, but since they are imported, their namespace shall be present otherwise non conformed to RFC7951:\n\ntypically will be something like (except that the spectrum yang does not permit that yet- i need to change it):\n\nmodule gnpy-api {\n  namespace \"urn:gnpy:api\";\n  prefix gnpy-api;\n\n  import gnpy-network-topology {\n    prefix gnt;\n  }\n  import gnpy-eqpt-config {\n    prefix gnl;\n  }\n  import gnpy-path-computation {\n    prefix gns;\n  }\n  import gnpy-spectrum {\n    prefix gnspect;\n\n  }\n\n  container api {\n    container topology {\n      uses gnt:topology;\n    }\n    container equipment {\n      uses gnl:eqpt;\n    }\n    container service {\n      uses gns:services;\n    }\n    container spectrum {\n      uses gnspect:spectrum;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nThen inside the json, the namespace of each module should appear (as they are in the example)",
